<section id="hero">
	<div class="hero-grid">
		<div class="hero-left">
			<h1 class="reveal">
				The System<br />
				<span>Is Rigged.</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="reveal" style="transition-delay: 0.15s">
				Wealth does not trickle down — it floods upward. The top 1% of the
				global population holds more combined wealth than the bottom 50%.
				This is not an accident. It is the designed outcome of a system
				built to extract value from workers and transfer it to capital
				owners. The data is unambiguous. The injustice is structural. The
				solution must be structural. And it must be collective.
			</p>
			<div class="callout">The data is unambiguous</div>
		</div>
		<div class="hero-right">
			<div class="stat-grid">
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-0">
					<div class="num" data-target="1" data-prefix="" data-suffix="%">1%</div>
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-0">
						Own more wealth than the bottom 50% combined
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-1">
					<div class="num" data-target="82" data-prefix="" data-suffix="%">82%</div>
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-1">
						Of new wealth generated in 2017 went to the top 1% — Oxfam,
						2018<button
							type="button"
							class="cite-ref"
							aria-label="View source: Oxfam 2018"
							aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false"
							data-source="Oxfam, Reward Work Not Wealth, 2018"
							data-url="https://www.oxfam.org/en/research/reward-work-not-wealth"
						>*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-2">
					<div class="num" data-target="700" data-prefix="" data-suffix="M">700M</div>
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-2">
						people trapped in extreme poverty under decades of capitalist
						'development'<button
							type="button"
							class="cite-ref"
							aria-label="View source: World Bank 2024"
							aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false"
							data-source="World Bank, Poverty and Shared Prosperity, 2024"
							data-url="https://www.worldbank.org/en/publication/poverty-and-shared-prosperity"
						>*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-3">
					<div class="num" data-target="5" data-prefix="$" data-suffix="T">$5T</div>
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-3">
						gained by global billionaires during COVID-19 (2020–2022)<button
							type="button"
							class="cite-ref"
							aria-label="View source: Oxfam 2022"
							aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false"
							data-source="Oxfam, Profiting from Pain, 2022"
							data-url="https://www.oxfam.org/en/research/profiting-pain"
						>*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-box stat-box-full" role="group" aria-labelledby="stat-label-4">
					<div class="num" data-target="1" data-prefix="Top " data-suffix="%">Top 1%</div>
					<div class="label" id="stat-label-4">
						Emit more CO₂ than the poorest 50% of humanity combined — the
						same class that owns half the world's wealth<button
							type="button"
							class="cite-ref"
							aria-label="View source: Oxfam 2025"
							aria-controls="cite-popover" aria-expanded="false"
							data-source="Oxfam, Carbon Inequality Kills, 2025"
							data-url="https://www.oxfam.org/en/research/carbon-inequality-kills"
						>*</button>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
